<P><TABLE WIDTH=80%>
<TR><TD ALIGN=center>The professed concern for freedom of the press in the West is not very
persuasive in the light of...the actual performance of the media in serving the powerful and
privileged as an agency of manipulation, indoctrination, and control. A "democratic
communications policy," in contrast, would seek to develop means of expression and
interaction that reflect the interests and concerns of the general population, and to
encourage their self-education and their individual and collective action.<BR><BR>
NOAM CHOMSKY
