<P><B><A HREF="interviews/9301-albchomsky.html">Conversations with Michael Albert</A></B> - An extensive 3-part discussion (1/93) - <A HREF="interviews/9301-albchomsky-1.html">Part I</A> | <A HREF="interviews/9301-albchomsky-2.html">Part II</A> | <A HREF="interviews/9301-albchomsky-3.html">Part III</A> | <A HREF="interviews/9301-albchomsky.html">All Parts</A> (165K)

<TD VALIGN=top>

<P><B><A HREF="other/intellectual-property.html">Chomsky on Intellectual Property</A></B> - Excerpts from <A HREF="year/year.html"><CITE>Year 501</CITE></A>

<P><B><A HREF="interviews/92-chase.html">Naomi Chase interviews Chomsky</A></B> on linguistics and human nature. (1992)

<P><B><A HREF="interviews/9201-propaganda.html">Chomsky on Propaganda</A></B> - From a WBAI interview (1/92)

<P><B><A HREF="interviews/dmt-capitalism.html">Noam Chomsky on Capitalism</A></B> - An interview from the <CITE>Detroit Metro Times</CITE>
<BR>Also includes a <B><A HREF="interviews/dmt-capitalism.html#sidebar">review of <CITE>Deterring Democracy</CITE></A></B> (1991?)

<P><B><A HREF="interviews/9111-middle-east.html">The Middle East Hour</A></B> (11/91)

<P><B><A HREF="interviews/9103-unjust-war.html">Chomsky on an Unjust War</A></B> - An interview on the Gulf War. (3/91)

<P><B><A HREF="interviews/db-8912.html">Interview with David Barsamian</A></B> - On the Cold War, economy, El Salvador, Israel (12/89)

<P><B><A HREF="interviews/8812-massey-qa.html">Q&A from the Massey Lectures</A></B> - Chomsky fields questions from a panel of journalists on his analysis of the media. (12/88)

<P><B><A HREF="interviews/86-silber.html">Chomsky debates John Silber</A></B> on U.S. intervention in Latin America. (1986)

<P><B><A HREF="other/85-hitchens.html">The Chorus and Cassandra</A></B> - Christopher Hitchens defends Chomsky on Cambodia, Faurisson, and the Middle East. (1985)

<P><B><A HREF="articles/8102-right-to-say.html">His Right to Say It</A></B> - Chomsky explains his defense of Faurisson. (1981)

<P><B><A HREF="articles/8010-free-expression.html">Some Elementary Comments on the Rights of Freedom of Expression</A></B> - Defense of Robert Faurisson's civil rights. (1980)

<P><B><A HREF="articles/7706-distortions.html">Distortions at Fourth Hand</A></B> - Chomsky and Herman on Cambodia in the media (1977)

<P><B><A HREF="other/intellectuals-state.html">Leninism and State Capitalism</A></B> - An excerpt from "Intellectuals and the State" (1977)

<P><B><A HREF="other/notes-on-anarchism.html">Notes On Anarchism</A></B> - Introduction to Daniel Gu&#233;rin's <CITE>Anarchism: From Theory to Practice.</CITE> (1970)

</TABLE>

<P ALIGN=center><TABLE BORDER CELLPADDING=5><TR><TD ALIGN=center><FONT SIZE=4>Under construction: <A HREF="mc/mc.html">Manufacturing Consent: Noam Chomsky and the Media</A></FONT>
<BR>A web version of the award-winning film and companion book. (The first two sections are complete.)</TABLE>

<CENTER>
<P><FONT SIZE=6 FACE="Arial"><B>About the Noam Chomsky Archive</B></FONT>

<P>New World Media and ZNet are proud to bring you a comprehensive collection of Chomsky's political work -- nearly <FONT COLOR="#800000"><I>ten</I></FONT> megabytes of text and <FONT COLOR="#800000"><I>three</I></FONT> hours of audio! The <A HREF="http://www.lbbs.org/">ZNet</A> web site hosts <A HREF="http://www.lbbs.org/zmag/index.htm">Z Magazine</A> and <A HREF="http://www.lbbs.org/sep/sep.htm">South End Press</A>, two major publishers of Chomsky's work. <A HREF="http://www.worldmedia.com/">New World Media</A> is working to build an online clearinghouse of progressive and left-libertarian media. Together, we're pleased to present one of the most in-depth educational resources on the web!

<P>We're constantly growing! More selections are on the way. Eventually we will also offer search capabilities and a system-wide index. Please <A HREF="/comment/comment2.htm">tell us what you think</A> about the archive so far!

<P><FONT SIZE=2>Note: Chomsky is on leave in South America this fall, but when he returns we will offer a schedule of his speaking appointments.</FONT>
</CENTER>

<PRE> </PRE>

<CENTER>
<P><FONT SIZE=5><B><A HREF="credits.html">History & Credits</A></B></FONT>


<P>If you like this archive, please subscribe to <A HREF="http://www.lbbs.org/zmag/index.htm">Z Magazine</A> and purchase books from <A HREF="http://www.lbbs.org/sep/sep.htm">South End Press</A>, <A HREF="http://www.akpress.org/">AK Press</A>, Common Courage Press, Hill and Wang, Odonian Press, and Black Rose Books!

