<DOCNO>WT12-B12-16</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA062-000353-B014-142</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://catholicworker.org:80/mission.htm 206.9.170.150 19970115200836 text/html 2777
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Date: Wednesday, 15-Jan-97 20:14:46 GMT
Server: WebSite/1.1e
Allow-ranges: bytes
Content-type: text/html
Last-modified: Sunday, 22-Oct-95 19:30:52 GMT
Content-length: 2580
</DOCHDR>

<html>

<head>

<title>The Mission</title>

</head>

<body background="/strip1.gif">

<p>
<table border=0 width=100%>
<tr><td><pre>          </pre></td>

	<td align=center>

<basefont size=5>
<FONT SIZE=+1>N</FONT>EW <FONT SIZE=+1>W</FONT>ORLD <FONT SIZE=+1>M</FONT>EDIA
<br>
<basefont size=4>
<i><FONT SIZE=+1>T</FONT>HE <FONT SIZE=+1>M</FONT>ISSION</i>
<p>

</td>
</tr>
<tr><td><pre>          </pre></td>

<td>
<h4><i>New World Media</i> seeks to build a digital infrastructure for global
social transformation and information sharing.
</h4>
<h3>The Vision</h3>

Global distributed computing represents a significant and powerful transformation
in the way that individuals and institutions interact and evolve.
<p>
Fundamentally,
the technology is <i>decentralized</i> -- consumers become publishers.  There are NO
true filters.<p>
The new
medium is creating <i>radically different economies in publishing information</i> --
alternative media can go global.<p>
<i>Globalization of the technology</i> means that individual communities of resistance can
build and sustain effective <i>networks of resistance</i>.
<p>
<h3>The Tools</h3>

This service has been inspired by the works of Noam Chomsky, one of the world's leading
intellectuals and scientists, not to mention his status as one of America's, if not the
world's, leading dissidents.
<p>
Chomsky's work in analyzing the media, domestic and foreign affairs has inspired many
to work for social change.  His work has also begun to transform the way we approach media,
particularly the task of alternative media.  Lastly, this service is deeply informed by
the belief that any true or significant social change takes place through thousands of
small and dedicated efforts by people across the globe.  This service aims to be one
such effort.
<p>
Most of the New World Media Web consists of a rich set of content, including what is
becomming one of the world's most comprehensive archives of Chomsky's works.  In
conjunction with those materials are numerous and growing resources from crucial
alternative media organizations from around the world.  In addition to content, the service
offers users traditional conferencing and chat, where users can interact, share ideas,
and hopefully even organize.  An upcoming feature will be a weekly current affairs section,
where New World Media staff spin the weeks news and events onto the Web.
<p>
We hope our effort can enrich your world!
<p>
Sincerely,
<p>
Jeremy Allaire<br>
New World Media


</table>
</DOC>
