<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN7" HREF="#TXT7">7</A></FONT> <CITE>Observer,</CITE> Sept. 26, 1993.

<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN8" HREF="#TXT8">8</A></FONT> Stephen Fidler, "Latin America `chaos' warning," <CITE>FT,</CITE> Sept. 25/26, 1993.

<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN9" HREF="#TXT9">9</A></FONT> Carothers, in Abraham Lowenthal, ed., <CITE>Exporting Democracy</CITE> (Johns Hopkins, 1991); <CITE>In the Name of Democracy</CITE> (U. of California, 1991).

<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN10" HREF="#TXT10">10</A></FONT> Howard French, <CITE>NYT,</CITE> Oct. 21, 1993.

<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN11" HREF="#TXT11">11</A></FONT> Keith Bradsher, "Administration Plans New Export Initiative," <CITE>NYT</CITE> business section, Sept. 28; Michael Frisby, <CITE>WSJ,</CITE> Sept. 29, 30; Barro, <CITE>WSJ,</CITE> Oct. 25, 1993.

<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN12" HREF="#TXT12">12</A></FONT> Josef Hebert, AP, Sept. 30, 1993.

<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN13" HREF="#TXT13">13</A></FONT> Howard, "The Hidden Welfare State," <CITE>Political Science Quarterly,</CITE> Fall 1993.

<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN14" HREF="#TXT14">14</A></FONT> For a review of public opinion studies, and the ways in which the facts have been falsified or suppressed, see Vicente Navarro, in Navarro, ed., <CITE>Why the United States does not have a National Health Program</CITE> (Baywood, 1992).

<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN15" HREF="#TXT15">15</A></FONT> Sylvia Nasar, <CITE>NYT,</CITE> Sept. 17, 1993.

<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN16" HREF="#TXT16">16</A></FONT> <CITE>Multinational Monitor,</CITE> Sept. 1993. South Centre, <CITE>Facing the Challenge</CITE> (Zed, 1993), 4.

<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN17" HREF="#TXT17">17</A></FONT> O'Shaughnessy, <CITE>Observer,</CITE> Sept. 12; Guillermo Fernandez A., <CITE>BI,</CITE> Sept.; Porpora, <CITE>Christian Science Monitor,</CITE> Oct. 20, 1993.

<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN18" HREF="#TXT18">18</A></FONT> "Children pay price in Nicaragua's New Order," <CITE>Third World Resurgence</CITE> (Malaya) No. 35, 1993.

<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN19" HREF="#TXT19">19</A></FONT> CEPAD <CITE>Report,</CITE> July-August 1993 (Evangelical Churches of Nicaragua); <CITE>Barricada,</CITE> Oct. 9, 10, 1993; <CITE>Envio</CITE> (Jesuit University of Central America, Managua), Sept. 1993; <CITE>Nicaragua News Service,</CITE> Nicaragua Network Education Fund, Washington, Oct. 2-9, 1993.

<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN20" HREF="#TXT20">20</A></FONT> Senate vote, Tim Johnson, Knight-Ridder Service, <CITE>BG,</CITE> Sept. 24; <CITE>Weekly News Update,</CITE> Nicaragua Solidarity Network, Sept. 26, Oct. 10; <CITE>Barricada,</CITE> Oct. 9, 1993.

<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN21" HREF="#TXT21">21</A></FONT> Daniels, "The Riddle of Russian Reform," <CITE>Dissent,</CITE> Fall 1993. See also Jonathan Steele, Roy Medvedev, <CITE>Guardian Weekly,</CITE> Oct. 3, 17; Fred Weir, <CITE>In These Times,</CITE> Oct. 18, 1993 (including a review of <CITE>Times</CITE> falsifications).

<P><FONT SIZE=2><A NAME="FN22" HREF="#TXT22">22</A></FONT> Alfred Malabre, <CITE>WSJ,</CITE> Sept. 13, 1993.

